<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-lg-8">
<h2>Whitespace in Webdesign: An Example</h2>
<p><small><span class="entypo-clock"></span> Published on May 19, 2014</small></p>
<p><i>Minimalist or modern designs tend toward more use of white space. White space or negative space is the space between design elements. On a macro level it's the space around the design and the large blocks of empty space between elements. On a micro level it's the space between two lines of text or the space between an image and its caption.</i></p>
<p>Read the article.</p>
<p><a target="_blank" href="http://debashisbarman.tumblr.com/post/86189526364/whitespace-in-webdesign-an-example">Whitespace in Webdesign: an Example</a></p>
